<div class="hidden part7">
    <p>Do digital texts considered a proper form of texts? I would argue that it is. Even if the information provided exists in a sphere of reality that are beyond physical form or any other kind of writing appliances can give. I want to argue that digital texts are an evolution of texts.</p>

    <p>That lamentation are nothing more than something fancy I thought about after I finished this series. I didn't think a series about being a librarian would make me this retrospective. <i>Magus of the Library</i>, however, has shown me that it is possible.</p>
</div>

